	   <tr><td colspan=2>Getting tired of the argument over who gets what. This is a nice bow and a halfway decent range item, but most people that I group with have better items in their range slot. Bow damage output is beased on dex, the higher the dex the more damage inflicted. Another factor is the type of arrow used, 10 damage arrows with a 20 damage bow = 30 damage system. High damage arrows are only economic when you get the EQ AA, until then just about everyone uses either summoned arrows or 1 damage cheap arrows to pull, nothing new there. Now my 2 cp (or more), if a group gets this to drop that group will decide how to dispose of it, posting the &quot;rangers should get it&quot; argument has no merit. If the ranger in the group that gets this to drop doesn't already have better, most people will let him loot it, if other melees are there and can use the thing and it has better stats than they have for a range slot, odds are they will roll. Most folks I know wont roll on an item they cant use if there is someone in the group that can use it, if no one can use, or if everyone has better and the item is droppable everyone rolls and the item ends up in a trader satchel on a mule in the bazaar. But arguing over loot definitely detracts from the game. ITS NOT REAL MONEY.<br>Uenladar 59 ranger on Mith Marr<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
